<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id7851bca1-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s583k–4"><num value="583k–4">§ 583k–4.</num><heading> Cooperative agreements</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="id7851bca2-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s583k–4/a"><num value="a" class="bold">(a)</num><heading class="bold"> In general</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Secretary may enter into a cooperative agreement with any State, tribal, local governmental, and private entity to carry out this subchapter.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="id7851bca3-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s583k–4/b"><num value="b" class="bold">(b)</num><heading class="bold"> Contents</heading><chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Cooperative agreements authorized under this section may—</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id7851bca4-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s583k–4/b/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> improve trail maintenance in a priority area;</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id7851bca5-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s583k–4/b/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> implement the strategy; or</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id7851bca6-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s583k–4/b/3"><num value="3">(3)</num><content> advance trail maintenance in a manner deemed appropriate by the Secretary.</content>
</paragraph>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="id7851bca7-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5">(<ref href="/us/pl/114/245/s6">Pub. L. 114–245, § 6</ref>, <date date="2016-11-28">Nov. 28, 2016</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/130/994">130 Stat. 994</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
